    "description": "Systematic grid refinement study using three structured hexahedral meshes (coarse 1.2M, medium 3.6M, fine 9.8M elements) applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry. Richardson extrapolation performed for velocity magnitude and wall shear stress at five operating points. Convergence criterion: GCI < 2% for QoI relevant to hemolysis index calculation. Residual convergence to 1e-6 for all transport equations verified across all mesh levels.",
    "activityType": "GridRefinementStudy",
